Li Na of  China  reached her first
French Open quarterfinals by beating Petra Kvitova of the Czech
Republic, 2-6, 6-1, 6-3.  She won the last six games of the match against the ninth
seed from the Czech Republic to become the first Chinese woman
to get among the last eight players at  Roland Garros . Li Na was
the first Chinese player to advance to a Grand Slam final when
she made the Australian Open championship match in January.  To contact the reporter on this story:
